YAML is a serialization language - standard format to trasmit over wire
  YAML Ain't Markup Language

  Syntax -
    1. key-value pairs
    2. Object -
    3. boolean
    4. lists
    5. multilinestring : >  --- also '|'
       This is line 1,
       This is line 2

    6. environment variables   $
    7. placeholders -{{}}
    8. multiple yaml files in a single file by separating three hypens ---



The file has 3 parts

1) Metadata
2) Specification - pertaining to kind(Deployment or Service)
3) Status - It is automatically updated by Kubernetes

Selectors and Labels  - To connect the service to deployment
